// Print Sin Wave One Period (#1302)

// No input. Prints a 5-row × 20-column ASCII approximation of one full sine wave period using `*` for plot points and `.` for empty. Use the formula `y = round(2 * sin(2π * x / 20)) + 2` for `x = 0..19` and plot `*` at `(y, x)`.

main

def main {
    stl.startup
    stl.output ".............*****..\n...........**.....**\n*.........*.........\n.**.....**..........\n...*****............\n"
    stl.loop
}
